$$
\begin{array}{l}
\text { [Solution] } 20 \div\left[\frac{3}{2+3}-\left(\frac{2 \times 3}{2+3}-1\right)\right] \\
=20 \div\left[\frac{3}{5}-\frac{1}{5}\right], \\
=20 \times \frac{5}{2}, \\
=50 \text { (kilometers); }
\end{array}
$$

Therefore, the answer is: 50 kilometers.

